AGI - The head of Russian security services (Fsb) accused Ukraine and the West of facilitating the attack near Moscow, claimed by the jihadist group Islamic State, with Russia insisting on a link between Kiev and alleged aggressors. "We believe that the action was prepared by both radical Islamic and, of course, facilitated by Western intelligence and the Ukrainian secret services themselves directly involved," said Alexander Bortnikov, quoted by Russian media. On Monday Vladimir Putin had admitted for the first time, three days after the events and accusations of Isis, that the alleged aggressors were "radical Islamic", pointing the finger against Ukraine.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
