Bortnikov in particular pointed his finger at the United States and Great Britain. When asked whether the United States, the United Kingdom and Ukraine were involved, he replied: I think it is. Although, he added, "the sponsor has not yet been identified". An hypothesis contradicted by Belarusian President Alexander Lukashenko, a close ally of Russia, who claimed that the attackers had initially attempted to flee to his country. "They couldn't get into Belarus. They saw this and then changed their way to the Russian-Ukrainian border."

